==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm}} {{term|thries|lang=enm}}, from earlier {{term|thrie|lang=enm}} (< {{etyl|ang}} {{term|þriga|þrīga|lang=ang}}) + adverbial {{term|-s}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/θraɪs/}} {{SAMPA|/TraIs/}}
* {{audio|en-us-thrice.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{rhymes|aɪs}}

===Adverb===
{{en-adv|-}}

# [[three]] [[time]]s

====Usage notes====
* Unlike {{term|once}} and {{term|twice}}, {{term||thrice}} is somewhat dated, often used for a comical or intentionally archaic effect. {{term||[[three|Three]] [[times]]}} is the more standard usage. On the other hand, {{term||once}} and {{term||twice}} are almost always preferred over {{term||[[one]] [[time]]}} and {{term||[[two]] [[times]]}} except when needed for parallel structure (e.g. when listing "one time, two times, three times"). {{term||Thrice}} does however retain some currency in compounds like {{term|thrice-monthly}}.

